<div class="row text-center m-3 my-5">
  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-3 p-2">
    <div class="card card-body m-1 h-100">
      <h5 class="card-title">The 50/30/20 rule</h5>
      <p class="card-text">Clover is based in the "50/30/20 budget rule", an easy-to-follow budgeting plan, because having a plan allows you to cover your expenses, doing the activities that make you happy.</p>
      </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-3 p-2">
    <div class="card card-body m-1 h-100">
      <h5 class="card-title">50% Essentials</h5>
      <p class="card-text "> Essentials are those bills that you absolutely must pay and are the things really necessary. These include rent, car payments, groceries, utilities, internet, insurance and health care.
    </p>
      </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-3 p-2">
    <div class="card card-body m-1 h-100">
      <h5 class="card-title">30% Life Style</h5>
      <p class="card-text">Life Style represents the things you spend money on that are not absolutely essential, but make your life better. This includes dinner, movies out, a streaming service and vacations.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-3 p-2">
    <div class="card card-body m-1 h-100">
      <h5 class="card-title">20% Priorities</h5>
      <p class="card-text">Try to allocate 20% of your net income to savings and investments just when you receive the money. This includes adding money to an emergency fund or a bank savings account and the stock market.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


